title JSON Encoding & Decoding Flow\n<size:11><i>Services_JSON — WordPress JSON serialization (deprecated since WP 5.3.0)</i></size>

|Encode Path|
start
:Caller invokes **encode($var)**;
note right
  Sets Content-Type: application/json
  header as a side effect.
  Use encodeUnsafe() to skip header
  (XSS warning applies).
end note
:Set Content-type header\n<i>application/json</i>;
:Call **encodeUnsafe($var)**;
:Save current LC_NUMERIC locale;
:Force LC_NUMERIC to **'C'**\n<i>(prevent locale decimal separator issues)</i>;
:Call **_encode($var)** — Type Dispatch;

|Encode Path|
if (Type of $var?) then (boolean)
    :Emit **'true'** or **'false'**;
elseif (null) then
    :Emit **'null'**;
elseif (integer) then
    :Emit cast int;
elseif (double / float) then
    :Emit cast float;
elseif (string) then
    :Iterate bytes via **strlen8()** / **substr8()**;
    if (Byte range?) then (ASCII ctrl\n0x08–0x0D)
        :Emit escape sequence\n<i>\\b \\t \\n \\f \\r</i>;
    elseif (quote / slash /\nbackslash) then
        :Emit escaped char;
    elseif (ASCII printable\n0x20–0x7F) then
        :Emit byte as-is;
    else (multibyte UTF-8\n2–6 byte sequences)
        |UTF Conversion|
        :Pack multibyte bytes;
        :Call **utf82utf16($utf8)**\n<i>mb_convert_encoding or manual bit-shift</i>;
        :sprintf **'\\uXXXX'** escape;
        |Encode Path|
        :Append Unicode escape to output;
    endif
    if (Incomplete multibyte\nsequence at end?) then (yes)
        :Emit replacement char **'?'**;
    else (no)
    endif
    :Return **'"'** + $ascii + **'"'**;
elseif (array — sequential) then
    :array_map **_encode()** on each element\n<i>[recursive]</i>;
    |Error Handling|
    if (Any element isError()?) then (yes)
        :Return error immediately\n<i>bubble up</i>;
        |Encode Path|
    else (no)
        |Encode Path|
        :Return **'['** + join(',') + **']'**;
    endif
elseif (array — associative\nor object) then
    if (SERVICES_JSON_USE_TO_JSON flag\nAND toJSON() exists?) then (yes)
        :Call **$var->toJSON()**;
        if (Result also has toJSON()?\n<i>recursion guard</i>) then (yes)
            |Error Handling|
            if (SUPPRESS_ERRORS flag?) then (yes)
                :Return **'null'**;
                |Encode Path|
            else (no)
                :Return **Services_JSON_Error**\n<i>infinite recursion detected</i>;
                |Encode Path|
            endif
        else (no)
            :Recursively call **_encode($recode)**;
        endif
    else (no)
        :get_object_vars($var)\nor use array keys/values;
    endif
    :array_map **name_value()** on\neach key-value pair;
    |Error Handling|
    if (Any property isError()?) then (yes)
        :Return error immediately\n<i>bubble up</i>;
        |Encode Path|
    else (no)
        |Encode Path|
        :Return **'{'** + join(',') + **'}'**;
    endif
else (unsupported type)
    |Error Handling|
    if (SERVICES_JSON_SUPPRESS_ERRORS?) then (yes)
        :Return literal **'null'**;
        |Encode Path|
    else (no)
        :Return **new Services_JSON_Error**\n<i>'type cannot be encoded'</i>;
        |Encode Path|
    endif
endif

:Restore LC_NUMERIC locale;
:Return encoded JSON string;
stop

|Encode Path|
note
  **name_value($name, $value):**
  1. _encode($value) → if isError: return error
  2. Return _encode(strval($name)) + ':' + encoded_value
end note

|Decode Path|
start
:Caller invokes **decode($str)**;
:Call **reduce_string($str)**\n<i>strip // comments, /* */ block comments, trim()</i>;

if (Literal value?\n<i>strtolower comparison</i>) then ('true')
    :Return PHP **true**;
    stop
elseif ('false') then
    :Return PHP **false**;
    stop
elseif ('null') then
    :Return PHP **null**;
    stop
else (not a literal)
endif

if (**is_numeric($str)**?) then (yes)
    :Return **int** or **float**\n<i>prefers int when float == int</i>;
    stop
else (no)
endif

if (Matches string pattern\n**/^([\"']).*\\1$/s**?) then (yes)
    :Extract inner chars via **substr8()**;
    :Iterate each byte;
    if (Byte type?) then (escape sequence\n\\b \\t \\n \\f \\r \\\" \\' \\\\ \\/)
        :Emit decoded char;
    elseif (Unicode escape\n\\uXXXX) then
        |UTF Conversion|
        :chr(hexdec) + chr(hexdec);
        :Call **utf162utf8($utf16)**\n<i>mb_convert_encoding or manual bit-shift</i>;
        |Decode Path|
        :Append UTF-8 char to $utf8;
    elseif (ASCII printable\n0x20–0x7F) then
        :Pass through as-is;
    else (multibyte UTF-8\nmasks 0xC0/0xE0/0xF0...)
        :substr8($chrs, $c, N)\npass through sequence;
    endif
    :Return $utf8 decoded string;
    stop
else (no)
endif

if (Matches array/object pattern\n**/^\\[.*\\]$/** or **/^\\{.*\\}$/**?) then (yes)
    :Initialize stack and container;
    if (Opening char?) then ('[')
        :Push **SERVICES_JSON_IN_ARR**\n$arr = [];
        note right: SERVICES_JSON_IN_ARR = 3
    else ('{')
        if (SERVICES_JSON_LOOSE_TYPE flag?) then (yes)
            :Push **SERVICES_JSON_IN_OBJ**\n$obj = [] <i>(associative array)</i>;
        else (no)
            :Push **SERVICES_JSON_IN_OBJ**\n$obj = new stdClass();
        endif
        note right: SERVICES_JSON_IN_OBJ = 4
    endif
    :Push initial SLICE marker\n<i>{what: SLICE, where: 0, delim: false}</i>;
    :reduce_string() on inner content;
    if (Empty content?) then (yes)
        :Return $arr or $obj immediately;
        stop
    else (no)
    endif

    :Begin **character-by-character state machine**;
    repeat
        if (Current state & char?) then (comma at SLICE level\nor end-of-string)
            :Extract slice = substr8(chrs, top.where, len);
            :Push new SLICE marker;
            if (Stack context?) then (IN_ARR)
                :array_push($arr, **decode($slice)**)\n<i>[recursive decode]</i>;
            else (IN_OBJ)
                if (Quoted key?) then (yes)
                    :key = decode(quoted_name)\nval = decode(trim(value));
                else (no / unquoted)
                    :key = raw_name\nval = decode(trim(value));
                endif
                if (LOOSE_TYPE?) then (yes)
                    :$obj[$key] = val;
                else (no)
                    :$obj->$key = val;
                endif
            endif
        elseif (quote char, not IN_STR) then
            :Push **IN_STR** with delimiter;
            note right: SERVICES_JSON_IN_STR = 2
        elseif (quote char, IN_STR,\nnot escaped) then
            :Pop **IN_STR**;
        elseif ('[' in SLICE/ARR/OBJ) then
            :Push **IN_ARR**;
        elseif (']' in IN_ARR) then
            :Pop **IN_ARR**;
        elseif ('{' in SLICE/ARR/OBJ) then
            :Push **IN_OBJ**;
        elseif ('}' in IN_OBJ) then
            :Pop **IN_OBJ**;
        elseif ('/*' in SLICE/ARR/OBJ) then
            :Push **IN_CMT**;
            note right: SERVICES_JSON_IN_CMT = 5
        elseif ('*/' in IN_CMT) then
            :Pop **IN_CMT**\nBlank out comment chars in $chrs;
        else (other char)
            :Advance position;
        endif
    repeat while (more chars?) is (yes)
    -> no;
    if (Final stack context?) then (IN_ARR)
        :Return **$arr** (PHP array);
    else (IN_OBJ)
        :Return **$obj** (stdClass or array);
    endif
    stop
else (no match)
    |Error Handling|
    :Return **Services_JSON_Error**\n<i>unrecognized input structure</i>;
    stop
endif

|Error Handling|
note
  **Services_JSON_Error:**
  - Extends PEAR_Error if PEAR is available,
    otherwise standalone class
  - **isError($data)** checks instanceof
    Services_JSON_Error or PEAR::isError()
  - Errors bubble up immediately from
    arrays and objects on first failure
  - SERVICES_JSON_SUPPRESS_ERRORS (flag=32):
    encode returns 'null' instead of error
end note

@enduml
